<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <title><%= title %></title>
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/@picocss/pico@2/css/pico.min.css" />
  </head>
  <body>
    <main class="container">
      <h1><%= title %></h1>
      <section>
        <article>
          <header>
            <strong>Signed in as:</strong> <%= user.email %> (<%= user.role %>)
          </header>
          <p>This lightweight dashboard is ready for custom analytics, user management, and webhook delivery logs.</p>
          <p>Extend <code>src/views/admin.ejs</code> and related routes to render live data from the database.</p>
        </article>
      </section>
      <section>
        <article>
          <h2>Next Steps</h2>
          <ul>
            <li>Expose API data via dedicated admin routes.</li>
            <li>Secure the dashboard with HTTPS and SSO where required.</li>
            <li>Integrate charts using your preferred front-end library.</li>
          </ul>
        </article>
      </section>
    </main>
  </body>
</html>
